5000|$|Technically, the Prophecy offered one-note <b>monophony,</b> several effects (including distortion, wave shaping, delay/reverb and chorus/flanger), and 128 memory {{locations}} for user sound programs. No sequencer was included, but its integrated arpeggiator {{was a source}} of [...] "instant gratification", as some magazines put it. A PCM/CIA slot allowed for offline storage of patches and banks. Standard MIDI sockets, a special socket for connecting an EC5 pedal bank, a sustain pedal socket, and a pair of audio outputs occupied the rear panel.|$|E
